{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Re-direct \u00a32.5bn prison fund into youth services",
        "additional_details": "Areas with the biggest youth service budget cuts have seen the sharpest increase in knife crime.\r\n\r\nFewer than 1 in 10 people think having more people in prison is the most effective way to deal with crime \r\n\r\n48% of adults re-offend within 1yr of release\r\n\r\nOffenders with 50+ previous offences are 36% more likely to re-offend when a short prison sentence is used vs community sentence\r\n\r\nPrison population increased 69% in last 30yrs\r\n\r\nSource: Prison Reform Trust, All-Party Parliamentary Group",
        "background": "Please:\r\nTake a long term view to prevent crime, rather than ineffectively 'treating' it through prisons. \r\n\r\nBy:\r\nRe-directing the \u00a32.5bn prison fund to youth services, which have seen a devastating 70% budget cut in the last decade (causing an increase in youth crime).",
